ability: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Power Blast
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [P] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

name: Chansey
flavorText: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Meowth

attacks.name: Pay Day
attacks.effect: Draw 1 card.

flavorText: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Butterfree

ability.name: Powder Heal
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

flavorText: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

attacks.name: Bubble Drain
attacks.effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

name: Mankey

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

name: Venusaur

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

name: Greninja

ability.name: Water Shuriken
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may do 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water.  When it spins them and throws them at high speed,  these stars can split metal in two.

name: Haunter

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

name: Onix
flavorText: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

name: Jigglypuff

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

attacks.name: Inferno
attacks.effect: Flip 3 coins. Take an amount of [R] Energy from your Energy Zone equal to the number of heads and attach it to your Benched [R] Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Snivy
flavorText: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

name: Volcarona

attacks.name: Volcanic
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [R] Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: Its burning body causes it to be unpopular in hot parts of the world, but in cold ones, Volcarona is revered as an embodiment of the sun.

name: Blastoise

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra [W] Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do −20 damage.

flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Cinccino

attacks.name: Do the Wave
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won’t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

name: Charmander

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.effect: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: It uses its whole body to photosynthesize when exposed to sunlight. Its shell is made from hardened soil.

name: Electivire

attacks.name: Exciting Voltage
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra [L] Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

ability.name: Lunar Plumage
ability.effect: Whenever you attach a  Energy from your Energy Zone to this Pokémon, heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Misdreavus

attacks.name: Confuse
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: This Pokémon startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

name: Skarmory

attacks.name: etal Arms
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

name: Chimchar
flavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

name: Togepi
flavorText: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

ability.name: Nightmare Aura
ability.effect: Whenever you attach a  Energy from your Energy Zone to this Pokémon, do 20 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Cherrim

attacks.name: Leech Seed
attacks.effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: After absorbing plenty of sunlight, Cherrim takes this form. It’s full of energy while it’s like this, and its liveliness will go on until sundown.

name: Raichu

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

ability.name: Resilience Link
ability.effect: If you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, this Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks.

flavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

name: Nosepass

attacks.name: Iron
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

flavorText: It moves less than an inch a year, but when it’s in a jam, it will spin and drill down into the ground in a split second.

name: Gible
flavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

name: Staraptor

ability.name: Defensive Whirlwind
ability.effect: This Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks from  Pokémon.

flavorText: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

name: Manaphy

attacks.name: Oceanic
attacks.effect: Choose 2 of your Benched Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, take a [W] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to that Pokémon.

flavorText: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Snorlax

attacks.name: Collapse
attacks.effect: This Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

attacks.name: Psydrive
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [P] Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Cyclizar

attacks.name: Overacceleration
attacks.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Overacceleration attack does +20 damage.

flavorText: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

name: Sprigatito

attacks.name: Cry for
attacks.effect: Put 1 random [G] Pokémon from your deck into your hand.

flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

name: Floatzel

attacks.name: Attack the ound
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Pawmot

ability.name: Counterattack
ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

name: Machamp

attacks.name: Power Press
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra [F] Energy attached, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: Ekans

attacks.name: Poison
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

name: Bidoof
flavorText: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Plasma
attacks.effect: Take a [L] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched [L] Pokémon.

flavorText: It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

name: Riolu
flavorText: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Exeggcute

attacks.name: Growth
attacks.effect: Take a [G] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs, it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

name: Froakie
flavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

name: Rayquaza

attacks.name: Spiral Rush
attacks.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

attacks.name: Draco
attacks.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random 4 times. For each time a Pokémon was chosen, do 40 damage to it.

attacks.name: Draco
attacks.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random 4 times. For each time a Pokémon was chosen, do 40 damage to it.

name: Mimikyu

attacks.name: Shadow Hit
attacks.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your Pokémon.

flavorText: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu’s old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

name: Cosmog

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.

name: Lycanroc

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

name: Alolan Exeggutor

attacks.name: Tropical Hammer
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Blazing sunlight has brought out the true form and powers of this Pokémon.

name: Alolan Ninetales
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Alolan Vulpix

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: A deity resides in the snowy mountains where this Pokémon lives. In ancient times, it was worshiped as that deity’s incarnation.

name: Crabrawler
flavorText: This Pokémon punches trees and eats the berries that drop down, training itself and getting food at the same time.

name: Alolan Grimer

attacks.name: Poison
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: There are a hundred or so of them living in Alola’s waste-disposal site. They’re all hard workers who eat a lot of trash.

name: Toucannon

attacks.name: Beak Blast
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

name: Zeraora

ability.name: Thunderclap Flash
ability.effect: At the end of your first turn, take a  Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

name: Kartana
flavorText: This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

name: Blacephalon

attacks.name: Beat Punk
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 70 damage to itself.

flavorText: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: Xurkitree

attacks.name: Electronica
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Dawn Wings Necrozma

attacks.name: Psychobilly
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: Lunala no longer has a will of its own. Now under the control of Necrozma, it continuously expels all of its energy.

name: Dusk Mane Necrozma

attacks.name: Black Metal
attacks.effect: Discard a [M] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: This is its form while it is devouring the light of Solgaleo. It pounces on foes and then slashes them with the claws on its four limbs and back.

name: Stakataka

attacks.name: Brass Rock
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

flavorText: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

attacks.name: Shoegaze
attacks.effect: Discard the top 5 cards of each player's deck.

name: Poipole

attacks.name: 2-Step
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

name: Stufful
flavorText: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

attacks.name: Plasma Hurricane
attacks.effect: Take a [L] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

name: Vanillite

attacks.name: Sweets Relay
attacks.effect: If 1 of your Pokémon used Sweets Relay during your last turn, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.

name: Jolteon

attacks.name: Beginning Bolt
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

name: Alcremie

attacks.name: Sweets Overload
attacks.effect: This attack does 40 damage for each time your Pokémon used Sweets Relay during this game.

flavorText: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it’s decorated with cream.

name: Dragonair

attacks.name: Shed
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

name: Audino

attacks.name: Drain Slap
attacks.effect: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

name: Togedemaru

attacks.name: Bristling Spikes
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack, do 30 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

flavorText: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: Greedent

attacks.name: Enhanced Fang
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Cleffa

attacks.name: Twinkly
attacks.effect: Put a random Pokémon from your deck into your hand.

flavorText: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

name: Horsea

attacks.name: ater
attacks.effect: This attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

name: Chinchou

attacks.name: uring
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

flavorText: Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.

name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Diving Swipe
attacks.effect: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

flavorText: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: ross-ut
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

attacks.name: Happy Punch
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, heal 60 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Marill
flavorText: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.

name: Weavile
flavorText: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.

name: Latias

attacks.name: Crossing Flights
attacks.effect: If Latios is on your Bench, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

name: Tropius

attacks.name: Double Smash
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.

name: Poliwag

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon’s innards showing through the skin.

name: Milotic

ability.name: Healing Ripples
ability.effect: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may heal 60 damage from 1 of your  Pokémon.

flavorText: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.

name: Zorua
flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: Zoroark

ability.name: Illusive Trickery
ability.effect: If your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from this Pokémon's attacks, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.

name: Miltank

attacks.name: Rolling Frenzy
attacks.effect: Until this Pokémon leaves the Active Spot, this Pokémon's Rolling Frenzy attack does +30 damage. This effect stacks.

flavorText: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it’s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.

name: Phanpy

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: This attack does damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon equal to the damage this Pokémon has on it.

flavorText: This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud, it won’t be able to settle down unless it washes its body.

ability.name: Veevee ’volve
ability.effect: This Pokémon can evolve into any Pokémon that evolves from Eevee if you play it from your hand onto this Pokémon. (This Pokémon can't evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.)

attacks.name: Blazing Beatdown
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra [R] Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

ability.name: Legendary Pulse
ability.effect: At the end of your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, draw a card.

name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

attacks.name: Volt Tackle
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Mimikyu

attacks.name: Try to
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

flavorText: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

name: Machamp

attacks.name: Hurricane Punch
attacks.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: Regigigas

attacks.name: Raging Hammer
attacks.effect: This attack does more damage equal to the damage this Pokémon has on it.

flavorText: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

name: Shaymin

ability.name: Fragrant Flower Garden
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

flavorText: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Absol

attacks.name: Leap
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

name: Venusaur

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

attacks.name: Giant Bloom
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Find a
attacks.effect: Put 1 random [G] Pokémon from your deck into your hand.

flavorText: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

name: Metapod
flavorText: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

name: Butterfree

ability.name: Powder Heal
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

flavorText: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

name: Weedle
flavorText: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.

name: Beedrill
flavorText: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

name: Oddish
flavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

name: Gloom
flavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

name: Vileplume

attacks.name: Soothing Scent
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It has the world’s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

name: Paras
flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

name: Parasect
flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

name: Venonat
flavorText: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokémon at night that are attracted by light.

name: Venomoth

attacks.name: Poison Powder
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

name: Bellsprout
flavorText: Even though its body is extremely skinny, it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.

name: Weepinbell
flavorText: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

name: Victreebel

ability.name: Fragrance Trap
ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, once during your turn, you may switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Basic Pokémon to the Active Spot.

flavorText: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs, it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

name: Exeggutor

attacks.name: Stomp
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.

attacks.name: Tropical Swing
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Tangela

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.effect: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Scyther
flavorText: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Double Horn
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

flavorText: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it’ll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

name: Petilil

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.effect: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.

name: Lilligant

attacks.name: Leaf Supply
attacks.effect: Take a [G] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched [G] Pokémon.

flavorText: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.

name: Skiddo

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Until recently, people living in the mountains would ride on the backs of these Pokémon to traverse the mountain paths.

name: Gogoat
flavorText: It can sense the feelings of others by touching them with its horns. This species has assisted people with their work since 5,000 years ago.

name: Charmander

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.effect: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

name: Charizard

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

attacks.name: Crimson Storm
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Vulpix

attacks.name: Tail
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

name: Ninetales

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.effect: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine

attacks.name: Heat Tackle
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

attacks.name: Inferno Onrush
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: It can’t run properly when it’s newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

name: Magmar
flavorText: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

name: Flareon

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.effect: Discard 1 [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Moltres

attacks.name: Sky Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It’s one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

attacks.name: Inferno
attacks.effect: Flip 3 coins. Take an amount of [R] Energy from your Energy Zone equal to the number of heads and attach it to your Benched [R] Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Heatmor
flavorText: There’s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

name: Salandit
flavorText: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Salazzle
flavorText: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

name: Sizzlipede
flavorText: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: Centiskorch

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.effect: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

name: Blastoise

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra [W] Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

attacks.name: Hydro Bazooka
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra [W] Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Psyduck

attacks.name: Headache
attacks.effect: Your opponent can't use any Supporter cards from their hand during their next turn.

flavorText: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

name: Golduck
flavorText: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.

name: Poliwag
flavorText: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon’s innards showing through the skin.

name: Poliwhirl
flavorText: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl’s has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

name: Poliwrath

ability.name: Counterattack
ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

name: Tentacool
flavorText: Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

name: Tentacruel

attacks.name: Poison Tentacles
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

name: Seel
flavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don’t bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

name: Dewgong
flavorText: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.

name: Shellder
flavorText: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

name: Cloyster

ability.name: Shell Armor
ability.effect: This Pokémon takes -10 damage from attacks.

flavorText: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

name: Krabby
flavorText: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

name: Kingler

attacks.name: KO Crab
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

name: Horsea
flavorText: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

name: Seadra

attacks.name: Water
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It’s the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

name: Goldeen
flavorText: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

name: Seaking

attacks.name: Horn Hazard
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

name: Staryu
flavorText: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you’ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.

name: Starmie
flavorText: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

name: Magikarp
flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.effect: Discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

name: Lapras

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 3 extra [W] Energy attached, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

name: Vaporeon

attacks.name: Bubble Drain
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

name: Omanyte
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Helix Fossil
flavorText: Because some Omanyte manage to escape after being restored or are released into the wild by people, this species is becoming a problem.

name: Omastar

attacks.name: Ancient Whirlpool
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell, Omastar couldn’t move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.

name: Articuno

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It’s said that this Pokémon’s beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.effect: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Ducklett
flavorText: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

name: Swanna
flavorText: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

name: Froakie
flavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

name: Frogadier
flavorText: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise  control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Greninja

ability.name: Water Shuriken
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may do 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water.  When it spins them and throws them at high speed,  these stars can split metal in two.

name: Pyukumuku
flavorText: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

name: Bruxish

attacks.name: Second Strike
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by this process from the protuberance on its head.

name: Snom
flavorText: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft, freshly fallen snow, so it will eat its way up a mountain, aiming for the peak.

name: Frosmoth

attacks.name: Powder Snow
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Frosmoth senses air currents with its antennae. It sends its scales drifting on frigid air, making them fall like snow.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Raichu

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.effect: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

attacks.name: Circle Circuit
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched [L] Pokémon.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Magneton

ability.name: Volt Charge
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may take a  Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Electrode
flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

name: Electabuzz

attacks.name: Thunder Punch
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage. If tails, this Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

name: Jolteon

attacks.name: Pin Missile
attacks.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

name: Zapdos

attacks.name: Raging Thunder
attacks.effect: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.

attacks.name: Thundering Hurricane
attacks.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

name: Zebstrika

attacks.name: Thunder
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: Eelektross

attacks.name: Thunder Fang
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: Helioptile
flavorText: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon’s electric moves.

name: Heliolisk

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.

name: Pincurchin

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: This Pokémon generates electricity when it digests food. It uses its five hard teeth to scrape seaweed off surfaces and eat it.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

name: Clefable
flavorText: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

name: Abra

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

name: Kadabra
flavorText: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

name: Alakazam

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

name: Slowbro
flavorText: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

name: Gastly
flavorText: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

name: Haunter
flavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

name: Gengar

attacks.name: Bother
attacks.effect: Your opponent can't use any Supporter cards from their hand during their next turn.

flavorText: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey’s shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

ability.name: Shadowy Spellbind
ability.effect: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't use any Supporter cards from their hand.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children’s are much tastier.

name: Hypno

ability.name: Sleep Pendulum
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

name: Mr. Mime

attacks.name: Barrier Attack
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes -20 damage from attacks.

flavorText: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

name: Jynx

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Its strange cries sound like human language. There are some musicians who compose songs for Jynx to sing.

name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Power Blast
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [P] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

attacks.name: Psydrive
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [P] Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Ralts
flavorText: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

name: Gardevoir

ability.name: Psy Shadow
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may take 1  Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to the  Pokémon in the Active Spot.

flavorText: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

name: Woobat
flavorText: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it’s evidence that Woobat live there.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won’t be able to fly for a little while.

name: Golett
flavorText: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

name: Golurk

attacks.name: Double Lariat
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

name: Sandshrew
flavorText: It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, the Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.

name: Sandslash
flavorText: The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pokémon’s spikes will feel when touched.

name: Diglett
flavorText: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

name: Dugtrio

attacks.name: Dig
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

name: Mankey
flavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

name: Primeape

attacks.name: Fight Back
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

name: Machop
flavorText: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machoke
flavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

name: Machamp
flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: Geodude
flavorText: Geodude that have lived a long life have had all their edges smoothed out until they’re totally round. They also have a calm, quiet disposition.

name: Graveler
flavorText: It climbs up cliffs as it heads toward the peak of a mountain. As soon as it reaches the summit, it rolls back down the way it came.

name: Golem

attacks.name: Double-Edge
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

flavorText: When Golem grow old, they stop shedding their shells. Those that have lived a long, long time have shells green with moss.

name: Onix
flavorText: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

name: Cubone

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do -20 damage.

flavorText: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

name: Marowak
flavorText: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

attacks.name: Bonemerang
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Hitmonlee

attacks.name: Stretch
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

name: Hitmonchan
flavorText: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

name: Rhyhorn
flavorText: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

name: Rhydon
flavorText: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

name: Kabuto
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Dome Fossil
flavorText: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.

name: Kabutops

attacks.name: Leech Life
attacks.effect: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

name: Clobbopus
flavorText: It’s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

name: Grapploct

attacks.name: Knock Back
attacks.effect: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

name: Ekans
flavorText: By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

name: Arbok

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

flavorText: The latest research has determined that there are over 20 possible arrangements of the patterns on its stomach.

name: Nidoran♀

attacks.name: Call for
attacks.effect: Put 1 random Nidoran♂ from your deck onto your Bench.

flavorText: Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they’ll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

name: Nidorina
flavorText: The horn on its head has atrophied. It’s thought that this happens so Nidorina’s children won’t get poked while their mother is feeding them.

name: Nidoqueen

attacks.name: Lovestrike
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 more damage for each of your Benched Nidoking.

flavorText: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

name: Nidoran♂
flavorText: The horn on a male Nidoran’s forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

name: Nidorino
flavorText: With a horn that’s harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.

name: Nidoking

attacks.name: Poison Horn
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: When it goes on a rampage, it’s impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it’s lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

name: Zubat
flavorText: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

name: Golbat
flavorText: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

name: Grimer

attacks.name: Poison Gas
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

name: Muk

attacks.name: Venoshock
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: It’s thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

name: Koffing
flavorText: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

name: Weezing

ability.name: Gas Leak
ability.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Poisoned.

flavorText: If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.

name: Mawile

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Pawniard will fearlessly challenge even powerful foes. In a pinch, it will cling to opponents and pierce them with the blades all over its body.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: This Pokémon commands a group of several Pawniard. Groups that are defeated in territorial disputes are absorbed by the winning side.

name: Meltan

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Take 1 [M] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

name: Melmetal

ability.name: Hard Coat
ability.effect: This Pokémon takes -20 damage from attacks.

flavorText: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

name: Dratini
flavorText: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

name: Dragonite

attacks.name: Draco
attacks.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random 4 times. For each time a Pokémon was chosen, do 50 damage to it.

flavorText: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.

name: Pidgeot

ability.name: Drive Off
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

name: Rattata
flavorText: Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life. If its incisors get too long, this Pokémon becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.

name: Raticate
flavorText: People say that it fled from its enemies by using its small webbed hind feet to swim from island to island in Alola.

name: Spearow
flavorText: Its reckless nature leads it to stand up to others—even large Pokémon—if it has to protect its territory.

name: Fearow

attacks.name: Drill Run
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Carrying food through Fearow’s territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!

name: Jigglypuff
flavorText: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

name: Wigglytuff
flavorText: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.

attacks.name: Sleepy Song
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Meowth

attacks.name: Pay Day
attacks.effect: Draw 1 card.

flavorText: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Persian

attacks.name: Shadow Claw
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

flavorText: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

name: Doduo
flavorText: A two-headed Pokémon that was discovered as a  sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.

name: Dodrio
flavorText: An enemy that takes its eyes off any of the three heads—even for a second—will get pecked severely.

name: Lickitung

attacks.name: Continuous Lick
attacks.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

flavorText: If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away, either.

name: Chansey
flavorText: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: Dizzy Punch
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

name: Tauros
flavorText: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

name: Ditto

attacks.name: opy
attacks.effect: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack. If this Pokémon doesn't have the necessary Energy to use that attack, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can’t maintain its disguise.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Porygon

ability.name: Data Scan
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may look at the top card of your deck.

flavorText: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be created via computer programming.

name: Aerodactyl
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Old Amber

attacks.name: Primal
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent shuffles their Active Pokémon back into their deck.

flavorText: This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

name: Minccino
flavorText: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

name: Cinccino

attacks.name: Do the Wave
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won’t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

name: Wooloo
flavorText: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

name: Dubwool
flavorText: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

name: Helix Fossil
ability: Play this card as if it were a 40-HP Basic [C] Pokémon.At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play.This card can't retreat.

name: Dome Fossil
ability: Play this card as if it were a 40-HP Basic [C] Pokémon.At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play.This card can't retreat.

name: Old Amber
ability: Play this card as if it were a 40-HP Basic [C] Pokémon.At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play.This card can't retreat.

name: Erika
ability: Heal 50 damage from 1 of your [G] Pokémon.

name: Misty
ability: Choose 1 of your [W] Pokémon, and flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, take a [W] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to that Pokémon.

name: Blaine
ability: During this turn, attacks used by your Ninetales, Rapidash, or Magmar do +30 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Koga
ability: Put your Muk or Weezing in the Active Spot into your hand.

name: Giovanni
ability: During this turn, attacks used by your Pokémon do +10 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Brock
ability: Take a [F] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to Golem or Onix.

name: Sabrina
ability: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

name: Lt. Surge
ability: Move all [L] Energy from your Benched Pokémon to your Raichu, Electrode, or Electabuzz in the Active Spot.

name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

name: Gloom
flavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Double Horn
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

flavorText: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Charmander

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.effect: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.effect: Discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

name: Lapras

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 3 extra [W] Energy attached, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

name: Electrode
flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

name: Alakazam

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

name: Diglett
flavorText: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

name: Cubone

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do -20 damage.

flavorText: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

name: Nidoqueen

attacks.name: Lovestrike
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 more damage for each of your Benched Nidoking.

flavorText: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

name: Nidoking

attacks.name: Poison Horn
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: When it goes on a rampage, it’s impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it’s lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

name: Golbat
flavorText: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

name: Weezing

ability.name: Gas Leak
ability.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Poisoned.

flavorText: If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.

name: Dragonite

attacks.name: Draco
attacks.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random 4 times. For each time a Pokémon was chosen, do 50 damage to it.

flavorText: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.

name: Pidgeot

ability.name: Drive Off
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

name: Meowth

attacks.name: Pay Day
attacks.effect: Draw 1 card.

flavorText: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.
