name: Mew

attacks.name: sy Report
attacks.effect: Your opponent reveals their hand.

flavorText: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

attacks.name: Crimson Storm
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Circle Circuit
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched [L] Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psydrive
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [P] Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Exeggcute

attacks.name: Growth
attacks.effect: Take a [G] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs, it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

name: Exeggutor

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.

attacks.name: Powerful Bloom
attacks.effect: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Snivy
flavorText: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

name: Servine
flavorText: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

name: Serperior

ability.name: Jungle Totem
ability.effect: Each  Energy attached to your  Pokémon provides 2  Energy. This effect doesn't stack.

flavorText: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior’s noble eyes.

name: Morelull
flavorText: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull’s head. The caps regrow overnight.

name: Shiinotic

attacks.name: Flickering Spores
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

name: Dhelmise

attacks.name: Energy Whip
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 3 extra [G] Energy attached, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

name: Ponyta

attacks.name: Stomp
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: It can’t run properly when it’s newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

name: Rapidash

attacks.name: Rising Lunge
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

name: Magmar

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: This Pokémon was called the Larva That Stole the Sun. The fire Larvesta spouts from its horns can cut right through a sheet of iron.

name: Volcarona

attacks.name: Volcanic
attacks.effect: Discard 2 [R] Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: Its burning body causes it to be unpopular in hot parts of the world, but in cold ones, Volcarona is revered as an embodiment of the sun.

name: Salandit

attacks.name: Venoshock
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Salazzle

attacks.name: Poison Claws
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

name: Magikarp

attacks.name: Leap
attacks.effect: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

attacks.name: Rampaging Whirlpool
attacks.effect: Discard a random Energy from among the Energy attached to all Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Vaporeon

ability.name: Wash Out
ability.effect: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a  Energy from 1 of your Benched  Pokémon to your Active  Pokémon.

flavorText: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

name: Finneon
flavorText: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.

name: Lumineon

attacks.name: Aqua
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokémon—its natural predators.

name: Chewtle
flavorText: Its large front tooth is still growing in. When the tooth itches, this Pokémon will bite another Chewtle’s horn, and the two Pokémon will tussle.

name: Drednaw

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Its massive, jagged teeth can crush a boulder in a single bite. This Pokémon has an extremely vicious disposition.

name: Cramorant

attacks.name: Dive
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Circle Circuit
attacks.effect: This attack does 10 damage for each of your Benched [L] Pokémon.

flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Raichu

attacks.name: Gigashock
attacks.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

name: Electabuzz

attacks.name: Thunder
attacks.effect: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

name: Joltik
flavorText: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It’s soaking up static electricity because it can’t produce a charge on its own.

name: Galvantula

attacks.name: Electroweb
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

flavorText: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

name: Dedenne

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It’s small and its electricity-generating organ is not fully developed, so it uses its tail to absorb electricity from people’s homes and charge itself.

name: Mew

attacks.name: sy Report
attacks.effect: Your opponent reveals their hand.

flavorText: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

attacks.name: Genome
attacks.effect: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Sigilyph

attacks.name: Spike Draw
attacks.effect: Draw a card.

flavorText: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians’ emissaries.

name: Elgyem
flavorText: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

name: Beheeyem

attacks.name: Mind Jack
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.

name: Flabébé

attacks.name: Hypnotic
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: This Pokémon can draw forth the power hidden within blooming wild flowers. It is particularly fond of red flowers.

name: Floette

attacks.name: Leaf Drain
attacks.effect: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon draws forth what power is left in withered flowers to make them healthy again. It holds a red flower.

name: Florges

attacks.name: Bloomshine
attacks.effect: Heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon creates an impressive flower garden in its territory. It draws forth the power of the red flowers around its neck.

name: Swirlix
flavorText: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn’t get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.

name: Slurpuff
flavorText: By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

name: Mankey

attacks.name: ocus ist
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

name: Primeape
flavorText: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

name: Geodude
flavorText: Geodude that have lived a long life have had all their edges smoothed out until they’re totally round. They also have a calm, quiet disposition.

name: Graveler
flavorText: It climbs up cliffs as it heads toward the peak of a mountain. As soon as it reaches the summit, it rolls back down the way it came.

name: Golem

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks.

flavorText: When Golem grow old, they stop shedding their shells. Those that have lived a long, long time have shells green with moss.

name: Aerodactyl ex
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Old Amber

ability.name: Primeval Law
ability.effect: Your opponent can't play any Pokémon from their hand to evolve their Active Pokémon.

name: Marshadow

attacks.name: Revenge
attacks.effect: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.

name: Stonjourner
flavorText: The elemental composition of the rocks that form its body were found to match the bedrock of a land far away from this Pokémon’s habitat.

name: Koffing

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Put 1 random Koffing from your deck onto your Bench.

flavorText: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

name: Weezing

attacks.name: Smokescreen
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

flavorText: If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

name: Venipede
flavorText: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species, but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.

name: Whirlipede

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: This Pokémon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.

name: Scolipede

attacks.name: Venoshock
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws’ toxic spikes.

name: Druddigon

ability.name: Rough Skin
ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

flavorText: Druddigon lives in caves, but it never skips sunbathing—it won’t be able to move if its body gets too cold.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.

attacks.name: Scattering Cyclone
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Tauros

attacks.name: Fighting Tackle
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 80  more damage.

flavorText: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: ontinuous Steps
attacks.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Chatot

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Draw a card for each card in your opponent's hand.

flavorText: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t attack it.

name: Old Amber
ability: Play this card as if it were a 40-HP Basic [C] Pokémon.At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play.This card can't retreat.

name: Pokémon Flute
ability: Put a Basic Pokémon from your opponent's discard pile onto their Bench.

name: Mythical Slab
ability: Look at the top card of your deck. If that card is a [P] Pokémon, put it into your hand. If it is not a [P] Pokémon, put it on the bottom of your deck.

name: Budding Expeditioner
ability: Put your Mew ex in the Active Spot into your hand.

name: Blue
ability: During your opponent's next turn, all of your Pokémon take −10 damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Leaf
ability: During this turn, the Retreat Cost of your Active Pokémon is 2 less.

name: Exeggutor

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.

name: Serperior

ability.name: Jungle Totem
ability.effect: Each  Energy attached to your  Pokémon provides 2  Energy. This effect doesn't stack.

flavorText: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior’s noble eyes.

name: Salandit

attacks.name: Venoshock
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Vaporeon

ability.name: Wash Out
ability.effect: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a  Energy from 1 of your Benched  Pokémon to your Active  Pokémon.

flavorText: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

name: Dedenne

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It’s small and its electricity-generating organ is not fully developed, so it uses its tail to absorb electricity from people’s homes and charge itself.

name: Marshadow

attacks.name: Revenge
attacks.effect: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.

attacks.name: Powerful Bloom
attacks.effect: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Rampaging Whirlpool
attacks.effect: Discard a random Energy from among the Energy attached to all Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Genome
attacks.effect: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Aerodactyl ex
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Old Amber

ability.name: Primeval Law
ability.effect: Your opponent can't play any Pokémon from their hand to evolve their Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Scattering Cyclone
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Budding Expeditioner
ability: Put your Mew ex in the Active Spot into your hand.

name: Blue
ability: During your opponent's next turn, all of your Pokémon take −10 damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Leaf
ability: During this turn, the Retreat Cost of your Active Pokémon is 2 less.

attacks.name: Genome
attacks.effect: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Aerodactyl ex
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Old Amber

ability.name: Primeval Law
ability.effect: Your opponent can't play any Pokémon from their hand to evolve their Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Powerful Bloom
attacks.effect: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Genome
attacks.effect: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Oddish

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.effect: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

name: Gloom
flavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

name: Bellossom
flavorText: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

name: Tangela
flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

name: Yanma
flavorText: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won’t miss prey—even those behind it.

attacks.name: Air Slash
attacks.effect: Discard a random Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Roselia
flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

name: Roserade

attacks.name: Poisonous Whip
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: It uses its whole body to photosynthesize when exposed to sunlight. Its shell is made from hardened soil.

name: Grotle
flavorText: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

name: Torterra

attacks.name: Frenzy Plant
attacks.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Frenzy Plant.

flavorText: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground dwelt a gigantic Torterra.

name: Kricketot
flavorText: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

name: Kricketune

attacks.name: Entrancing Melody
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces a captivating sound.

name: Burmy
flavorText: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: Wormadam

attacks.name: Leaf Cutter
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: Combee

attacks.name: all for
attacks.effect: Put 1 random Basic Pokémon from your deck onto your Bench.

flavorText: At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a hundred, packed closely together in a lump.

name: Vespiquen
flavorText: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.

name: Carnivine

attacks.name: Flog
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: Leafeon

attacks.name: Leafy Cyclone
attacks.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of sunshine, you’ll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.

name: Mow Rotom

attacks.name: Energy Cutoff
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: The lawn mower is one of the household appliances that led to the development of the Rotom Dex.

name: Shaymin

ability.name: Fragrant Flower Garden
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

flavorText: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Magmar

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Take a [R] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

name: Magmortar

attacks.name: Bursting Inferno
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Slugma
flavorText: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.

name: Magcargo

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

name: Chimchar
flavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

name: Monferno
flavorText: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

attacks.name: Flare Blitz
attacks.effect: Discard all [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Heat Rotom

attacks.name: Heat Breath
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: If the convection microwave oven is not working properly, then the Rotom inhabiting it will become lethargic.

name: Swinub
flavorText: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

name: Piloswine

ability.name: Thick Fat
ability.effect: This Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks from  or  Pokémon.

flavorText: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

name: Mamoswine

ability.name: Thick Fat
ability.effect: This Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks from  or  Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a while, it was thought to have gone extinct.

name: Regice

ability.name: Crystal Body
ability.effect: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

name: Prinplup
flavorText: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

name: Empoleon

attacks.name: Aqua Jet
attacks.effect: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

name: Buizel
flavorText: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.

name: Floatzel

attacks.name: Jet Screw
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Shellos
flavorText: It used to have a shell on its back long ago. This species is closely related to Pokémon like Shellder.

name: Gastrodon

attacks.name: Muddy Water
attacks.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: They normally inhabit rocky seashores, but in times of continuous rain, they can sometimes be found in the mountains, far from the sea.

name: Finneon

attacks.name: Elegant Swim
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.

name: Lumineon
flavorText: With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokémon—its natural predators.

name: Snover

attacks.name: Ice Shard
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a [F] Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain’s lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

name: Abomasnow
flavorText: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

name: Glaceon

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

name: Wash Rotom
flavorText: This Rotom has entered a washing machine. It nods with satisfaction after it floods the surrounding area.

name: Frost Rotom

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.effect: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This Rotom has entered a refrigerator. It leaps around gleefully after it uses cold air to freeze the area around it.

attacks.name: Dimensional Storm
attacks.effect: Discard 3 [W] Energy from this Pokémon. This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Manaphy

attacks.name: Oceanic
attacks.effect: Choose 2 of your Benched Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, take a [W] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to that Pokémon.

flavorText: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Magneton
flavorText: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

name: Magnezone

attacks.name: Thunder Blast
attacks.effect: Discard a [L] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

name: Voltorb

attacks.name: Big Explosion
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Electrode
flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

name: Electabuzz

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Take a [L] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

name: Electivire

attacks.name: Exciting Voltage
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra [L] Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

name: Shinx

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

name: Luxio
flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

name: Luxray

attacks.name: Volt
attacks.effect: Discard all [L] Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.

attacks.name: Sparking Gadget
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Rotom

attacks.name: Assault Laser
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

name: Togepi
flavorText: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

name: Togetic
flavorText: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

name: Togekiss

attacks.name: Overdrive Smash
attacks.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Overdrive Smash attack does +60 damage.

flavorText: These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they’ve hardly been seen at all.

name: Misdreavus
flavorText: This Pokémon startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

attacks.name: Magical Delusion
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Ralts

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

name: Duskull
flavorText: If it finds bad children who won’t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it’s said.

name: Dusclops
flavorText: It seeks drifting will-o’-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.

name: Dusknoir

ability.name: Shadow Void
ability.effect: As often as you like during your turn, you may choose 1 of your Pokémon that has damage on it, and move all of its damage to this Pokémon.

flavorText: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.

name: Drifloon

attacks.name: Expand
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

flavorText: It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

name: Drifblim
flavorText: Some say this Pokémon is a collection of souls burdened with regrets, silently drifting through the dusk.

name: Uxie

attacks.name: Mind Boost
attacks.effect: Take a [P] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to Mesprit or Azelf.

flavorText: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: Mesprit

attacks.name: Supreme Blast
attacks.effect: You can use this attack only if you have Uxie and Azelf on your Bench. Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Azelf

attacks.name: sychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: Giratina

ability.name: Levitate
ability.effect: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

flavorText: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

name: Cresselia

attacks.name: Moonlight Gain
attacks.effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Rhyhorn
flavorText: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

name: Rhydon
flavorText: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

name: Rhyperior

attacks.name: Mountain Swing
attacks.effect: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck.

flavorText: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

name: Gligar
flavorText: It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

name: Gliscor

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: Hitmontop
flavorText: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

name: Nosepass
flavorText: It moves less than an inch a year, but when it’s in a jam, it will spin and drill down into the ground in a split second.

name: Regirock

ability.name: Exoskeleton
ability.effect: This Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

flavorText: Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.

name: Cranidos
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Skull Fossil
flavorText: A primeval Pokémon, it possesses a hard and sturdy skull, lacking any intelligence within.

name: Rampardos

attacks.name: Head Smash
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, this Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

flavorText: In ancient times, people would dig up fossils of this Pokémon and use its skull, which is harder than steel, to make helmets.

name: Wormadam
flavorText: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: Riolu
flavorText: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Lucario

ability.name: Fighting Coach
ability.effect: Attacks used by your  Pokémon do +20 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.

name: Hippopotas
flavorText: It shuts its nostrils tight, then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

name: Hippowdon
flavorText: It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.

attacks.name: Energized Blade
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Honchkrow

attacks.name: Skill
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.

name: Sneasel

attacks.name: ouble Scratch
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

attacks.name: Scratching Nails
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Poochyena
flavorText: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

name: Mightyena
flavorText: It will always obey the commands of a skilled Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.

name: Stunky
flavorText: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.

name: Skuntank

attacks.name: Poison Gas
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.

name: Spiritomb

attacks.name: Swirling
attacks.effect: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

name: Skorupi
flavorText: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

name: Drapion

attacks.name: Cross Poison
attacks.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

name: Croagunk

attacks.name: Group Beatdown
attacks.effect: Flip a coin for each Pokémon you have in play. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

name: Toxicroak

attacks.name: Group Beatdown
attacks.effect: Flip a coin for each Pokémon you have in play. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.

name: Darkrai

attacks.name: Dark Void
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.

ability.name: Nightmare Aura
ability.effect: Whenever you attach a  Energy from your Energy Zone to this Pokémon, do 20 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Skarmory

attacks.name: etal Arms
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

name: Registeel
flavorText: Registeel’s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.

name: Shieldon
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Armor Fossil
flavorText: A mild-mannered, herbivorous Pokémon, it used its face to dig up tree roots to eat. The skin on its face was plenty tough.

name: Bastiodon

ability.name: Guarded Grill
ability.effect: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokémon takes −100 damage from that attack.

flavorText: The bones of its face are huge and hard, so they were mistaken for its spine until after this Pokémon was successfully restored.

name: Wormadam

attacks.name: Iron Head
attacks.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor’s back contained a mysterious power.

name: Bronzong

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

flavorText: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: Probopass

attacks.name: Triple Nose
attacks.effect: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: Although it can control its units known as Mini-Noses, they sometimes get lost and don’t come back.

attacks.name: Metallic Turbo
attacks.effect: Take 2 [M] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Heatran

attacks.name: Steel Tackle
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Gible
flavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

name: Gabite
flavorText: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.

name: Garchomp

ability.name: Reckless Shearing
ability.effect: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw a card.

flavorText: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away, either.

attacks.name: Licking Fury
attacks.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Porygon
flavorText: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be created via computer programming.

name: Porygon2
flavorText: This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.

name: Porygon-Z

attacks.name: Buggy Beam
attacks.effect: Change the type of the next Energy that will be generated for your opponent to 1 of the following at random: [G],[R],[W],[L],[P],[F],[D], or [M].

flavorText: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z’s behavior.

name: Aipom
flavorText: As it did more and more with its tail, its hands became clumsy. It makes its nest high in the treetops.

name: Ambipom

attacks.name: Double Hit
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that’s proof it really likes you.

attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Shaymin

ability.name: Sky Support
ability.effect: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, your Active Basic Pokemon's Retreat Cost is 1 less.

flavorText: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

ability.name: Forest Breath
ability.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may take a  Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your  Pokémon.

ability.name: Snowy Terrain
ability.effect: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, do 10 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Linear
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Defensive Unit
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

attacks.name: Ultimate Force
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

ability.name: Fabled Luster
ability.effect: This Pokémon can't be affected by any Special Conditions.

name: Irida
ability: Heal 40 damage from each of your Pokémon that has any [W] Energy attached.

name: Celestic Town Elder
ability: Put 1 random Basic Pokémon from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Barry
ability: During this turn, attacks used by your Snorlax, Heracross, and Staraptor cost 2 less [C] Energy.

name: Adaman
ability: During your opponent's next turn, all of your [M] Pokémon take −20 damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.

ability.name: Forest Breath
ability.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may take a  Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your  Pokémon.

ability.name: Snowy Terrain
ability.effect: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, do 10 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Defensive Unit
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

attacks.name: Ultimate Force
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

ability.name: Fabled Luster
ability.effect: This Pokémon can't be affected by any Special Conditions.

attacks.name: Ultimate Force
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

ability.name: Fabled Luster
ability.effect: This Pokémon can't be affected by any Special Conditions.

name: Weedle

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Put 1 random Weedle from your deck onto your Bench.

flavorText: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

name: Kakuna

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.

attacks.name: Crushing Spear
attacks.effect: Discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Guillotine Rush
attacks.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Sprigatito

attacks.name: Cry for
attacks.effect: Put 1 random [G] Pokémon from your deck into your hand.

flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

name: Floragato
flavorText: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

name: Meowscarada

attacks.name: Fighting Claws
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

name: Charmander
flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Take 3 [R] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

name: Magmar
flavorText: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

name: Magmortar

attacks.name: Smoke Bomb
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

flavorText: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Paldean Tauros

attacks.name: Blaze Tackle
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: When heated by fire energy, its horns can get hotter than 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Those gored by them will suffer both wounds and burns.

name: Tentacool
flavorText: Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

name: Tentacruel
flavorText: When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

name: Buizel
flavorText: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.

name: Floatzel

attacks.name: ater
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Wiglett

attacks.name: Spring
attacks.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random. Do 30 damage to it.

flavorText: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

attacks.name: Pop Out
attacks.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random 3 times. For each time a Pokémon was chosen, do 50 damage to it.

name: Dondozo

attacks.name: Ocean Cyclone
attacks.effect: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

name: Tatsugiri

ability.name: Retreat Directive
ability.effect: Your Active Dondozo has no Retreat Cost.

flavorText: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.effect: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Electrode

attacks.name: Tumbling Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Plasma
attacks.effect: Take a [L] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched [L] Pokémon.

flavorText: It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

name: Pawmi
flavorText: It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

name: Pawmo
flavorText: When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.

name: Pawmot

ability.name: Counterattack
ability.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

name: Abra
flavorText: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

name: Kadabra
flavorText: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

name: Alakazam

attacks.name: Psychic Suppression
attacks.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any Energy attached.

flavorText: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

name: Mr. Mime

attacks.name: Juggling
attacks.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

name: Drifloon
flavorText: It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

name: Drifblim
flavorText: It can generate and release gas within its body. That’s how it can control the altitude of its drift.

attacks.name: Chaotic Impact
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

ability.name: Broken-Space Bellow
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may take a  Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

name: Gimmighoul

attacks.name: Unknown
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

name: Machop
flavorText: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machoke

attacks.name: Pummel
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

name: Machamp

attacks.name: Power Press
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra [F] Energy attached, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: Hitmonlee
flavorText: This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

name: Hitmonchan
flavorText: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

name: Riolu
flavorText: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

attacks.name: Aura Sphere
attacks.effect: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Flamigo

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

flavorText: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

name: Ekans
flavorText: By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

name: Arbok

attacks.name: Venomous Fang
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: After stunning its opponents with the pattern on its stomach, it quickly wraps them up in its body and waits for them to stop moving.

name: Paldean Wooper

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

name: Paldean Clodsire ex
card_type: Pokémon - Stage 1 - Evolves from Paldean Wooper

attacks.name: Venoshock
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Spiritomb

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

name: Shroodle
flavorText: Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.

name: Grafaiai

ability.name: Poison Coating
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

name: Tinkatink
flavorText: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

name: Tinkatuff

attacks.name: Tenacious Hammer
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.

attacks.name: Terrific Thumping
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Varoom
flavorText: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

name: Revavroom

attacks.name: Spinning Drift
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders— now numbering eight—to generate energy.

name: Gholdengo

attacks.name: Scintillating Surfing
attacks.effect: Flip a coin for each [M] Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokémon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.

name: Rattata
flavorText: Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life. If its incisors get too long, this Pokémon becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.

name: Raticate
flavorText: People say that it fled from its enemies by using its small webbed hind feet to swim from island to island in Alola.

name: Jigglypuff
flavorText: It hugely inflates its stomach and sings a mysterious melody. If you hear this melody, you’ll become sleepy right away.

name: Wigglytuff

ability.name: Comforting Song
ability.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away, either.

name: Lickilicky
flavorText: Lickilicky’s strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky’s tongue can stretch so far.

name: Bidoof
flavorText: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

attacks.name: Carefree Press
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Buneary
flavorText: If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the Pokémon is in need of care.

name: Lopunny
flavorText: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds with superdestructive kicks.

name: Cyclizar

attacks.name: Overacceleration
attacks.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Overacceleration attack does +20 damage.

flavorText: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

name: Iono
ability: Each player shuffles the cards in their hand into their deck, then draws that many cards.

name: Pokémon Center Lady
ability: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon, and it recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Red
ability: During this turn, attacks used by your Pokémon do +20 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon ex.

name: Team Rocket Grunt
ability: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 70 more damage.
